## 6. Sprint Board Entry (`/pro/planning/sprint-board`)

### Screen 2.1 — Sprint Board — Capability View

**This is the primary planning workspace.** The founder spends most of their Sprint Planning time here.

### Persistent Header (always visible throughout Sprint Planning)

A slim, sticky header strip at the top of the Sprint Board — always visible, never dismissable:

- Sprint identifier: Q1 2026
- Locked Sprint Goal — displayed in a compact styled strip
- Label (small, muted): `SPRINT GOAL`

This is the north star. Every initiative the founder creates should be oriented toward making this statement true.

---

### Reference Strip

A collapsible panel positioned below the persistent header and above the board columns. Collapsed by default.

**Collapsed state:**
Single line: `Q1 synthesis context — your 12-month focus areas and sequencing insight` + expand chevron

**Expanded state:**
Three `CalloutBlock` instances (reuse existing CalloutBlock component):
- `LOAD-BEARING AREAS` — 2-3 capability areas from the 12-month synthesis
- `DEPENDENCY CHAIN` — the sequencing insight from the Roadmap Review
- `PRIMARY CONSTRAINT` — the single thing most likely to slow this sprint

Read-only. Visual treatment: subtle background fill, compressed type, clearly secondary.

Data source: Roadmap Review 12-month synthesis fields stored in Supabase.

---

### Sprint Board — Column Layout

Three equal-width columns. Same color coding as Quarter Map (blue / green / orange). Each column contains exactly three capability cards — pre-loaded from the locked Quarter Map selections.

**Column headers:**
- `Prioritize` — subtitle: `Core focus — 0/3 capabilities planned`
- `Plant` — subtitle: `Groundwork — 0/3 capabilities planned`
- `Progressively Iterate` — subtitle: `Refinement — 0/3 capabilities planned`

Subtitle counters update in real time as initiatives are added.

---

### Capability Cards in the Board

Each capability card in the Sprint Board shows:

| Element | Content |
|---|---|
| Column color indicator | Left border in column color (blue/green/orange) |
| Capability name | Full name |
| Dimension tag | e.g., `Financial Health` in dimension color |
| Maturity score | Percentage — from M&R Audit |
| Stage status badge | Below Stage / At Stage / Ahead of Stage |
| Initiative count | `0 initiatives` — updates as initiatives are added |
| Status indicator | `Not started` → `In progress` → `Complete` |
| CTA | `Build Initiatives →` |

Clicking `Build Initiatives →` opens the Capability Context screen (Section 7).

---

### Progress Indicator

Above the columns, a persistent progress counter:
`0 of 9 capabilities have initiatives defined`

Updates in real time. When all nine are complete: `9 of 9 capabilities planned — ready to lock.`

---

### View Toggle

Top-right of the board: `By Capability | By Initiative`

- **By Capability** — default view (as described above)
- **By Initiative** — flat list of all initiatives across all tiers. Available once at least one initiative exists. Sortable by tier, capability, or owner. Keep existing implementation from Image 9-10 — the collapsed and expanded initiative list is correct.

User preference saved to profile after first manual toggle. Default for new sessions: By Capability until the user has toggled at least once.

---

### Header Controls

Top-right of the Sprint Board (separate from view toggle):
- `Save Draft` — saves current state without locking. Always active.
- `Lock Sprint →` — primary action. Disabled until all nine capabilities have at least one initiative. Active when complete.

