---

### Screen 4.2 — Pre-Lock Review

**Accessed via:** `Review & Lock Sprint →` button (appears when all nine capabilities have at least one initiative)

**Layout:** Clean full-width screen. Not a modal.

**Top section — Sprint Goal (prominent, styled):**
The locked sprint goal displayed as a committed statement. Visual weight here is intentional.

**Middle section — Three reflection questions (static display — no inputs, no checkboxes):**

These are displayed as a structured block of statements the founder reads:

1. *"Do the Prioritize initiatives, if successful, make the sprint goal meaningfully true?"*
2. *"Do the Plant initiatives lay real groundwork for future sprints — or are they actually priorities in disguise?"*
3. *"Are the Iterate refinements genuinely light-touch — or are they competing for the same attention as your Prioritize work?"*

No interaction required. These are reflection prompts. The founder reads them and decides to proceed or go back.

**Bottom section — Conscious deprioritization (read-only):**
Label (muted): `CONSCIOUSLY DEPRIORITIZED THIS SPRINT`
A clean list of the sixteen capability areas NOT engaged this sprint — pulled from the full 25 minus the nine Quarter Map selections.
Supporting line: *"These 16 capability areas are intentionally out of scope this sprint. This is a choice, not an oversight."*

**Actions:**
- Secondary: `← Back to Board` — returns to Sprint Board
- Primary: `Lock My Sprint →` — triggers lock sequence

---

### Screen 5.1 — Loading State

Standard `LoadingOverlay` component. Message: *"Building your sprint synthesis..."*

On lock:
1. Validate all nine capabilities have at least one initiative
2. Save all initiatives, refinements, and milestones to Supabase with status: `locked`
3. Save parked items if any with status: `parked`
4. Trigger GPT synthesis via n8n webhook — payload: sprint goal, nine capabilities + 3P assignments, all initiative outcome statements, all milestone statements, user stage, Q1 sprint theme, Contextual Overrides from Roadmap Review
5. Listen for synthesis completion via Supabase Realtime (same pattern as Roadmap Review)

---

### Screen 5.2 — Sprint Posture Synthesis (Completion Moment)

A full-screen completion moment. The sprint becomes real here.

**Header:**
- Label (small caps, muted): `YOUR SPRINT PLAN — Q1 2026`
- Sprint goal displayed in full as a committed statement, framed

**Sprint Posture Statement:**
Three to five sentences of GPT-generated synthesis reflecting back what the locked plan represents as a whole.

Addresses:
- What the Prioritize initiatives are building toward
- What the Plant initiatives are seeding for future sprints
- What the Iterate refinements are keeping aligned
- One neutral observation if relevant (a tension, a sequencing note, a capacity consideration) — framed as an observation, never a judgment

Tone: peer-level strategic advisor, observational, not congratulatory.

For Phase 2: stage-aware template paragraph referencing actual initiative names and sprint goal language. Must reference real data — no lorem ipsum.

**Sprint Plan Summary (below synthesis):**
Three labeled sections:

*Prioritize — Building Toward:*
Three capabilities, each with initiative name(s) and milestone count

*Plant — Seeding for Future Sprints:*
Three capabilities, each with initiative name and binary done definition

*Progressively Iterate — Keeping Aligned:*
Three capabilities, each with refinement name and time box

This is the clean artifact version — scannable, presentable to a team or coach.

**Actions:**
- `Download Sprint Plan (PDF)` — deferred to PDF build phase. Button present, shows "Coming soon" state or disabled state.
- `Launch My Sprint →` — primary CTA. Routes to `/pro/execution`. Supporting line (small, muted): *"You'll track progress, manage milestones, and run your sprint review in the Execution section."*

