## 10. Team Members Table

A lightweight supporting feature required for initiative and milestone owner assignment.

### Table Structure (`team_members`)

| Column | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `id` | UUID | Primary key |
| `user_id` | UUID | Foreign key — scoped to account |
| `first_name` | Text | Required |
| `last_name` | Text | Required |
| `position` | Text | Optional — role or title |
| `created_at` | Timestamp | |
| `updated_at` | Timestamp | |

Account-scoped — each founder's team is their own. No cross-account sharing.

### Owner Assignment Field Behavior

Any `owner` field on an initiative or milestone uses a dropdown or typeahead pulling from this table. Never a free-text field. Owner field stores the team member `id`, not their name — ensures all references remain linked to one clean record.

If no team members exist when the owner field is first encountered: a subtle inline prompt: `+ Add a team member` — opens a lightweight add modal (first name, last name, position). The new record is saved and immediately available in the dropdown.

### Team Members Management

A team members management view — accessible from user settings or a settings link within the Sprint Board. Allows:
- Add team member
- Edit team member
- Delete team member (soft delete — does not break existing initiative assignments)

This is a simple list view. No advanced permissions, roles, or multi-user access in v1.

