## 11. Sprint History & Version Management

*Flagged for future build — data architecture must support it now.*

Every sprint is its own Supabase record with:
- Sprint version stamp
- Quarter identifier
- Status: `draft` / `locked` / `completed`
- All associated initiatives, milestones, and refinements linked by sprint ID

Edits to locked sprints in the Execution section create new versions rather than overwriting. Original locked version is preserved.

A sprint history view — accessible from the Pro Suite navigation — will allow founders to browse, review, and manage past sprints. Soft delete only. Not in scope for this build — but the schema must support it from day one.

