## 13. Tone & Language Principles

All platform-generated content in Sprint Planning follows the same principles established across the platform:

- **Observational not prescriptive** — reveals implications, never directs
- **Stage-calibrated** — every piece of generated content references the user's actual AE Ladder stage by name
- **Non-evaluative** — the platform does not judge initiative quality as good or bad
- **Specific** — references real capability names, real initiative names, real sprint goal language
- **Peer-level voice** — strategic advisor, not coach or educator
- **Tiered weight** — the tone of form fields and prompts reflects the effort level of each 3P tier. Prioritize feels deliberate. Plant feels tactical. Iterate feels light.

